G.L. c. 212, \u00a7 3.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this action pursuant to G.L. c. 212, § 3, as the amount in controversy exceeds $25,000 and involves allegations of negligence under Massachusetts law.

G.L. c. 223, \u00a7 1.proposition: Venue is proper in Bristol County pursuant to G.L. c. 223, § 1, as the events giving rise to this action occurred in Brockton, Massachusetts, which is located in Bristol County.

G.L. c. 231, \u00a7 85.proposition: Defendant’s breaches of duty are actionable under Massachusetts law, including G.L. c. 231, § 85, which establishes the general principles of negligence and liability.
